    "sections": [
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Introduction",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.1",
            "summary": "This supervisory statement is addressed to all UK firms that fall within the scope of Solvency II, and the Society of Lloyd’s. It sets out the Prudential Regulation Authority’s (PRA’s) expectations of",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.2",
            "summary": "Guidelines on supervision of branches of third-country insurance undertakings are covered in supervisory statement 44/15.3",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.3",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.4",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.5",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.6",
            "summary": "Firms should also refer to:",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.7",
            "summary": "Any reference to any provision of direct EU legislation is a reference to it as it forms part of retained EU law.",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Compliance with the Guidelines",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.1",
            "summary": "[Deleted].",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.2",
            "summary": "The PRA expects firms to comply with all of the Set 2, System of Governance and ORSA Guidelines (as at the end of the transition period) that apply to them, in a proportionate manner.",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.3",
            "summary": "This supervisory statement also provides further commentary on certain Guidelines where the PRA considers that this is useful for firms. Those Guidelines on which further commentary is provided are:",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Recognition and valuation of assets and liabilities other than technical provisions",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.1",
            "summary": "The PRA expects firms to comply with each of the Guidelines in all cases unless they intend to take advantage of the derogation in [Rule 5.4 in the Valuation Part](/pra-rules/valuation#2da42945a668420",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.2",
            "summary": "This derogation lays down criteria which, if met, allow a firm to recognise and value an asset or liability based on the valuation method it uses in preparing its annual or consolidated financial stat",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "3.3",
            "summary": "Where firms intend to take advantage of the Valuation 5.4 derogation, they should still apply Guidelines 1, 2, 4, 5 and 8 to 11. They should al",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "[Deleted]",
        "paragraphs": []
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "[Deleted]",
        "paragraphs": []
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Reporting and public disclosure",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "6.1",
            "summary": "In accordance with the requirement of the PRA Rulebook, Composites 4.5, composite firms are required to prepare a statement on the basis of the accounts referred to in Composites 3.2 identifying the e",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Single solvency and financial condition report (SFCR)",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "7.1",
            "summary": "The PRA expects firms to assess risks on a forward-looking basis, covering business plan and strategy timelines, and reflect the specific risk profile and governance mechanisms of each entity or group",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "7.2",
            "summary": "In SS26/15 the PRA has set out its expectations for non-life firms regarding the option of demonstrating that their risks have been projected to the ultimate time horizon.9 Firms should ensure that th",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "7.3",
            "summary": "As part of its supervisory process, the PRA will review ORSA reports on a risk-based and proportionate basis.",
            "as_at_date": "17/12/2021"
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "section_count": 7,
